in best practice after we finished a branch
and make our merge, we should delete it
and preventing confusion in future!

git branch --merged     //when we are in main
                        //show all branched that merged into the main!
                        //so if we sure we are finished with these branches
                        //we can delete them


git branch --no -merged  //show all branches that not merged
                         //on current branch
                         //if we are in main
                         //it's show all branches that not merged on main!
                         //(they our current development)

Note: git branch --no-merged bugfix/signup-form     //we are in main
                                                    //it show all branches that not merged on "bugfix/signup-form"

      git branch merged bugfix/signup-form          //we are in main
                                                    //it show all branches that merged on "bugfix/signup-form"
